svg.text: Optimal Kalman Filtering for Tip-Tilt Correction

• Filtering shows performance improvements!• Can further improve by: • tuning noise model - specific to a telescope • tuning LQR cost parameters • tighter/more expensive fit to turbulence• Can test against standard integrator on-sky • Can also incorporate control action error in filter

• Vibrations show up as peaks on a power spectrum• Can fit autoregressive model to each peak: identify frequency and damping ratio from position, spread• Batch identification: look at PSD every 1000 timesteps• Can check/adjust in closed loop whether vibrations are being completely controlled

• Kalman filter overlaps physics-model expectations, actual measurements• Useful to reduce measurement error and make predictions for TT control• Provides optimal linear state observer for Linear-Quadratic-Gaussian control• Depends heavily on accurate physics model: have to learn online and fit
